## 1. INTRODUCTION

### 1.1 Purpose

This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document provides a comprehensive description of UniPDF Studio, an advanced web-based PDF management and editing platform. It serves as the foundational blueprint for the development lifecycle and addresses multiple stakeholder needs.

**Intended Audience:**

- **Development Team:** Technical requirements, architectural guidelines, and implementation specifications
- **Project Evaluators:** Technical merit assessment, feasibility evaluation, and academic review
- **Future Maintainers:** Design philosophy, implementation details, and system documentation
- **End Users:** System capabilities, limitations, and quality standards

This document establishes clear communication by defining technical requirements, functional specifications, and performance expectations for all project stakeholders.

### 1.2 Scope

UniPDF Studio is a comprehensive browser-based application that transforms how users interact with PDF documents. The system eliminates the need for desktop software installation, providing professional-grade PDF manipulation tools through modern web browsers.

**Core Capabilities:**

The system provides robust PDF viewing, editing, and annotation functionalities comparable to commercial desktop applications. Users can work with multiple file formats:

- **PDF Files:** Native support with full editing capabilities
- **Microsoft Word:** DOCX format processing and conversion
- **Images:** JPEG, PNG, TIFF support for conversion and insertion
- **Text Formats:** Plain text and HTML document handling

**Innovative Features:**

**Artificial Intelligence Integration:** The system leverages OpenAI's GPT-4 for intelligent document analysis. Users can generate summaries of lengthy documents, ask natural language questions about content, and receive contextually relevant answers. Smart text rewriting capabilities automatically rephrase content to match different tone requirements, complexity levels, or length constraints.

**Optical Character Recognition:** Automatic detection of scanned documents with conversion to searchable and editable content. Supports 50+ languages with sophisticated image pre-processing including deskewing, denoising, and contrast enhancement for improved accuracy.

**File Management Operations:**

- Merge multiple PDFs into single documents
- Split large files by page range, bookmarks, or intervals
- Rearrange pages through drag-and-drop interfaces
- Compress files with adjustable quality settings
- Password protection using AES-256 encryption

**Cloud Collaboration Features:**

Documents are stored securely in cloud infrastructure with access from any device. Real-time collaboration allows multiple users to simultaneously edit documents with instant synchronization. Version control tracks document evolution and enables restoration of previous versions.

**Out of Scope (Phase 1):**

- Native mobile applications (iOS/Android)
- Offline desktop version
- Enterprise SSO integration
- Advanced vector graphic design capabilities

### 1.3 Project Objective

UniPDF Studio is driven by five fundamental objectives addressing critical gaps in document processing:

**1. Accessibility**

Provide professional PDF editing accessible from any device with a web browser. This democratizes access to tools traditionally locked behind expensive licenses, ensuring students, professionals, and remote workers can accomplish document tasks efficiently from any location.

**2. Cost-Effectiveness**

Offer a free alternative to expensive desktop software like Adobe Acrobat (which costs $180+/year). The platform leverages modern cloud computing and open-source technologies to deliver professional features at minimal cost.

**3. Innovation**

Integrate AI and OCR technologies for intelligent document processing. Unlike conventional software focused on manual editing, UniPDF Studio incorporates intelligent automation that understands content, extracts insights, and enhances productivity through features like AI summarization and conversational document queries.

**4. Collaboration**

Enable real-time team collaboration on PDF documents. Multiple users can simultaneously edit documents, discuss changes through integrated commenting, and track evolution through comprehensive version control, transforming document editing into a team-enabled process.

**5. Simplicity**

Minimize learning curves through intuitive interface design. Users should accomplish basic tasks within minutes without extensive training, while advanced capabilities remain accessible to expert users.

**Success Metrics:**

- Upload and edit PDF within 60 seconds of first visit
- System uptime: 99.9% reliability
- Support documents up to 100MB and 1,000 pages
- OCR accuracy: 90%+ for clear scans
- User satisfaction: 4.5/5 stars or higher

### 1.4 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **AI** | Artificial Intelligence - Machine learning models for text processing, trained on vast datasets to perform natural language understanding and generation |
| **API** | Application Programming Interface - Standardized protocols enabling system components and external services to exchange data and functionality |
| **DOCX** | Microsoft Word document format (Office Open XML) for text processing |
| **JWT** | JSON Web Token - Industry-standard authentication mechanism for secure identity transmission between client and server |
| **OCR** | Optical Character Recognition - Technology converting image-based text into searchable and editable content |
| **PDF** | Portable Document Format - Adobe's standardized format preserving document formatting across all platforms |
| **REST** | Representational State Transfer - Architectural style for web service interfaces using standard HTTP methods |
| **SRS** | Software Requirements Specification - Formal documentation of system requirements and technical specifications |
| **UI/UX** | User Interface / User Experience - Visual elements and overall interaction quality |
| **WebSocket** | Protocol enabling real-time bidirectional communication between browsers and servers for instant updates |

### 1.5 Overview

This document is organized in logical progression from high-level concepts to detailed specifications:

**Section 2 - Overall Description:** Product perspective, major features, user classes, operating environment, and dependencies

**Section 3 - Functional Requirements:** Detailed capabilities organized by modules with input/output specifications and acceptance criteria

**Section 4 - Non-Functional Requirements:** Performance, security, usability, reliability, and scalability standards

**Section 5 - System Models:** Use case diagrams, data flow diagrams, and entity relationship models providing visual system representations

