## 5. System Models

### 5.1 Use Case Diagrams

#### **Use Case 1: Student Workflow**
```
┌───────────┐
│  Student  │
└─────┬─────┘
      │
      ├──> Upload scanned lecture notes
      │         │
      │         ├──> Run OCR to extract text
      │         │
      │         └──> Export as searchable PDF
      │
      ├──> Open assignment PDF
      │         │
      │         ├──> Edit and add text
      │         │
      │         └──> Highlight important sections
      │
      └──> Merge multiple PDFs into one document
                │
                └──> Download final PDF
```

#### **Use Case 2: Business Professional Workflow**
```
┌──────────────────┐
│   Professional   │
└────────┬─────────┘
         │
         ├──> Upload contract PDF
         │         │
         │         ├──> Review and annotate
         │         │
         │         └──> Add comments for team
         │
         ├──> Share with colleagues
         │         │
         │         ├──> Set permission (comment only)
         │         │
         │         └──> Set expiration date
         │
         └──> Password protect document
                   │
                   └──> Download encrypted PDF
```

#### **Use Case 3: AI-Powered Analysis**
```
┌───────────┐
│    User   │
└─────┬─────┘
      │
      ├──> Upload 100-page research paper
      │         │
      │         └──> Click "Summarize" button
      │                   │
      │                   └──> AI generates 300-word summary
      │
      ├──> Ask question: "What are the key findings?"
      │         │
      │         └──> AI responds with answer + page references
      │
      └──> Select complex paragraph
                │
                └──> Use "Simplify" to rewrite
                          │
                          └──> Review and accept rewritten text
```

