### 5.3 Entity Relationship Diagram
```
┌──────────────┐         ┌──────────────┐         ┌──────────────┐
│     USER     │────────<│   DOCUMENT   │>────────│   VERSION    │
│              │  owns   │              │  has    │              │
│ - _id        │         │ - _id        │         │ - _id        │
│ - email      │         │ - title      │         │ - versionNum │
│ - password   │         │ - owner (FK) │         │ - document   │
│ - name       │         │ - fileUrl    │         │ - fileUrl    │
│ - role       │         │ - fileSize   │         │ - createdAt  │
│ - storage    │         │ - pages      │         └──────────────┘
└──────┬───────┘         │ - ocrText    │
       │                 └──────┬───────┘
       │                        │
       │                        │ has
       │                        ▼
       │                 ┌──────────────┐
       │                 │   COMMENT    │
       │                 │              │
       │                 │ - _id        │
       └─────────────────│ - document   │
         authors         │ - author (FK)│
                         │ - text       │
                         │ - page       │
                         └──────────────┘
```

---

## Conclusion

UniPDF Studio aims to democratize PDF editing by providing professional-grade tools accessible to anyone with a web browser. By combining traditional PDF manipulation with modern AI and OCR technologies, the system offers a comprehensive solution for students, professionals, and educators. The modular architecture ensures scalability and maintainability, while the cloud-first approach enables seamless collaboration and access from any device.

**Key Success Factors:**
1. Intuitive user interface requiring minimal training
2. Fast performance with responsive editing tools
3. Reliable cloud storage with 99.9% uptime
4. Intelligent AI features that add real value
5. Strong security and privacy protection

**Timeline:**
- Phase 1 (Months 1-3): Core PDF editing and file operations
- Phase 2 (Months 4-5): AI features and OCR integration
- Phase 3 (Month 6): Collaboration and cloud features
- Testing and Deployment (Month 6)

